# todo-core

todo-core is a simple API allowing consumers to view, add, update and delete their tasks.

All operations use the task data object. It has following attributes:

+ id - unique ID of the task in form of a string, assigned by system
+ text - arbitrary text content of a task, assigned by user

# todo-core API Root [/todos]

## List all tasks [GET]

Returns all tasks on the server.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            [
                {
                    "text":"Pay the bill.",
                    "id":"7b5be1f4-78f9-4e32-8b75-a7e87afec329"
                },
                {
                    "text":"Clean up the car.",
                    "id":"952daf28-1ff6-4a98-8a82-635480693aa4"
                }
            ]

## Retrive a single task [GET/{task_id}]

Returns a task object by it's ID if found.


+ Parameters
    + task_id (required, string, `"0b3211d3-76c6-456d-8971-20aa277bfc76"`) ... ID of the Task is a system generated random string

+ Response 200 (application/json)

                {
                    "text":"Call mom!",
                    "id":"0b3211d3-76c6-456d-8971-20aa277bfc76"
                }

## Create a new task [POST]

You may create your own task using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing a task.

+ text (string) - Arbitrary text content
+ id (string) - optional, will be ignored. A new id will be assigned 

+ Request (application/json)

            {
                "text":"Call mom!",
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /741340b7-1d03-45ac-a828-0d1430747b34

    + Body

            {
                "text":"Call dad!",
                "id":"741340b7-1d03-45ac-a828-0d1430747b34"
            }

## Update an existing task [PUT/{task_id}]

You may update an existing task using this action. It takes a JSON
object containing a task.

+ text (string) - Arbitrary text content
+ id (string) - ID of an existing task

+ Parameters
    + task_id (required, string, `"0b3211d3-76c6-456d-8971-20aa277bfc76"`) ... ID of the Task is a system generated random string

+ Request (application/json)

            {
                "text":"New text!",
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /741340b7-1d03-45ac-a828-0d1430747b34

    + Body

            {
                "text":"New text!",
                "id":"741340b7-1d03-45ac-a828-0d1430747b34"
            }
            
## Delete an existing task [DELETE/{task_id}]

You may delete an existing task using this action.


+ Parameters
    + task_id (required, string, `"0b3211d3-76c6-456d-8971-20aa277bfc76"`) ... ID of the Task is a system generated random string

+ Response 200 (application/json)